WEBVTT

00:02.966 --> 00:05.000
♪ Batman ♪

00:09.138 --> 00:12.306
<i> Gotham City.</i>
<i> Metropolis of wonders.</i>

00:12.608 --> 00:15.675
<i> Architectural queen</i>
<i> of the world.</i>

00:15.677 --> 00:20.279
<i> A new jewel is about to be</i>
<i> added to her crown.</i>

00:20.281 --> 00:23.615
Distinguished guests,
ladies and gentlemen.

00:23.617 --> 00:25.516
The mightiest bridge
in the world

00:25.518 --> 00:28.218
'becomes a part of our city.'

00:29.454 --> 00:33.856
I hereby dedicate this
engineering triumph

00:33.858 --> 00:37.226
the Amerigo Columbus bridge.

00:37.828 --> 00:38.860
<i> 'And in Wayne Manor'</i>

00:38.862 --> 00:41.629
<i> 'stately home of</i>
<i> millionaire Bruce Wayne'</i>

00:41.631 --> 00:44.898
<i> 'and his youthful ward,</i>
<i> Dick Grayson..'</i>

00:44.900 --> 00:48.167
Bruce, quick.
Come here and look.

00:48.169 --> 00:49.201
'What is it, Dick?'

00:49.203 --> 00:51.636
In the crowd there.
I just saw the Bookworm.

00:51.638 --> 00:53.604
- Are you sure?
- How can I mistake him?

00:53.606 --> 00:56.673
Those crazy clothes that look
like rare old book bindings.

00:56.675 --> 01:00.209
And I'm pretty sure he had on
his trick eye-glasses, too.

01:00.211 --> 01:02.678
The ones with the secret
radio stuff built in.

01:02.680 --> 01:05.346
Strange. What would a crook
like the Bookworm

01:05.349 --> 01:07.282
be doing at the dedication
of a bridge?

01:07.284 --> 01:11.653
Let's watch. Maybe he'll show
his nasty nose again.

