01:20.762 --> 01:22.629
Bookworm to Printer's Devil.

01:22.631 --> 01:24.864
'Bookworm to Printer's Devil.'

01:25.432 --> 01:27.499
Start chapter one.

01:27.501 --> 01:30.902
'Devil to Bookworm.
Got you boss.'

01:34.238 --> 01:34.904
Holy homicide.

01:34.906 --> 01:38.274
- 'Tell me it's a nightmare.'
- 'Steady, Dick.'

01:38.276 --> 01:39.341
It happened, all right.

01:39.343 --> 01:42.410
Commissioner Gordon killed.

01:42.544 --> 01:47.848
This is one time we don't
wait for the Bat-phone.

01:47.850 --> 01:50.183
Oh, my dears,
my dears.

01:50.185 --> 01:53.753
I was watching in the music
room. Did you see it, too?

01:53.755 --> 01:55.621
We did indeed, Aunt Harriet.

01:55.623 --> 02:00.025
I just hope <i> they</i> were
watching the television.

02:00.093 --> 02:01.226
'They?'

02:01.228 --> 02:03.361
Batman and Robin.

02:03.363 --> 02:06.163
'Who else can save us now?'

02:06.165 --> 02:07.130
Don't worry, Aunt Harriet.

02:07.132 --> 02:09.164
I guess there's not much
those two miss.

02:09.167 --> 02:11.167
Come on, Dick,
let's drive into the city

02:11.169 --> 02:14.203
and pay our respects
to a late, great man.

02:14.205 --> 02:15.871
Right, Bruce.

02:16.005 --> 02:18.539
It's the least we can do.

02:25.213 --> 02:27.981
I solemnly swear by my oath
as a crime fighter

02:27.983 --> 02:31.284
that this outrage
will not go unavenged.

02:32.319 --> 02:34.186
To the Bat-poles.

